#: ../../themes.rst:3
msgid "Themes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:5
msgid ""
"One of the nice things of django Organice is that themes are handled as "
"separate projects.  In fact, they are pluggable Django apps composed of "
"assets and templates that you can simply install and activate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:9
msgid "Official Themes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:11
msgid "Here is a list of django Organice themes officially supported by us:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:13
msgid "RSSK Theme: `django-organice-theme-rssk`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:14
msgid "Fullpage Theme: `django-organice-theme-fullpage`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:16
msgid ""
"If you have a nice theme and would like to include it in this list `let us "
"know by e-mail`_ or make a pull request on this page of the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:20
msgid "Mother Theme"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:22
msgid ""
"``django-organice-theme`` is the mother of all themes for django Organice.  "
"This theme is installed automatically when you install django Organice.  "
"From the development perspective all themes are derived from the mother "
"theme, which contains a collection of static files (assets) and templates, "
"as well as a ``Makefile`` for asset management. The mother theme is composed"
" of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:27
msgid "`bootstrap-sass`_ (Sass version of Twitter Bootstrap v3)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:28
msgid "`Compass`_ (CSS authoring framework using Sass)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:29
msgid "`UglifyJS v2`_ (JavaScript minifier)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:31
msgid ""
"The ``Makefile`` also supports you with updating those components on your "
"development system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:34
msgid "Rolling Your Own Theme"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:36
msgid "Preparations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:38
msgid ""
"Visit http://organice.io/themes and find a theme that is as close as it gets"
" of what you want."
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:39
msgid ""
"Go to that theme's repository page, make a copy of the whole project, and "
"rename it (e.g. to ``mytheme``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:41
msgid "Loop until you're happy:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:43
msgid ""
"Add or adapt the style sheet (``.scss``), JavaScript (``.js``), and other "
"files in ``mytheme/static/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:44
msgid ""
"Run ``make assets`` in order to compile the Sass files to CSS, and combine "
"and minify both CSS und JavaScript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../themes.rst:45
msgid ""
"Adapt the template files in ``mytheme/templates/``, and test the results on "
"your development system."
msgstr ""
